  "text": "Note that the visco-hyperelastic model proposed herein is based on a local additive decomposition of the stress tensor into initial and non-equilibrium parts. Based on previous studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , the ligament is assumed to have a Kelvin-Voigt-type viscoelastic constitutive behaviour. On the contrary, the model in [CITATION_4] supposes the additive split of the stress tensor into equilibrium and non-equilibrium parts assuming Maxwell-type viscoelastic behaviour for blood vessels. Motivated by [CITATION_5] and in order to consider different contributions of the matrix material and families of fibers on the non-equilibrium part, we divide the internal variables in",
